review_blob: Mild bluecheese with hint of nutmeg in taste. Nose very clean and flowery. Definetly one of best saisons I have had. (27.09.14) @ De Molen festival
Italian excellence at work. Good across the board. Like clean nose and straight taste. Blue cheese coming through as dominant with hint of nut.
First reaction was, this is interesting. Very fresh, easy drinking. Floral notes, modest soureness.
No smell (maybe too cold). Clear with limited head. Nicely smoky, but rye does not come through. Sort of same plain taste I am not too comfortable with.
Wonderful surprise in such a modest package. Color is almost the best quality of this beer. Finish is better then journey.
beer_name: Beer Hunters Mufloni Saison De Randonneur (4.5%)

review_blob: I would expect more from imperial stout. Aftertaste does not carry through, leaving pieces in your mouth.
